snippet.textDisplay:
I agree with how Jame's parents thought and their ideals for healthy eating, but seriously. I'm not saying it was bad, no, I'm just saying that it would have been a better idea to limit rather than exclude. It seems a bit smarter to let sugar be present sometimes, but make it a rarity to help show limitation and self-regulation. Personally my parents did the same thing, so I only got sodas once a week and sugary snacks like TimTams and MMs weren't very often in the cabinet. I still keep up those habits, because, well...
I'm still a kid living in a house that gets the wheat hog dot buns.
And I love them.
Fite meh.
